Procedure
1. Create the File
•	Go to Remix IDE
•	In the "File Explorers" tab (left sidebar), click the "Create New File" icon.
•	Name it SimpleWallet.sol

paste the code below
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
// SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
pragma solidity ^0.8.0;
contract SimpleWallet {  
    // Mapping to store user balances
    mapping(address => uint256) private balances;
    // Event to log deposits
    event FundsDeposited(address indexed user, uint256 amount);

    // Function to deposit Ether
    function deposit() public payable {
        balances[msg.sender] += msg.value;
        emit FundsDeposited(msg.sender, msg.value);
    }
    // Function to check balance
    function getBalance() public view returns (uint256) {
        return balances[msg.sender];
    }
}
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

2. Compile
3. Deploy
•	Click the Deploy & Run Transactions icon
•	Environment: Select Remix VM (Cancun) or London. This gives you fake test accounts with 100 ETH each.
•	Contract: Make sure SimpleWallet is selected.
•	Click Deploy.
4. Interact (Store & Retrieve)
•	Once deployed, look at the "Deployed Contracts" section at the bottom left. 
•	To Store (Deposit):
1.	Go up to the Value box (under "Gas Limit").
2.	Type 1 and change the dropdown from Wei to Ether.
3.	Click the red/orange deposit button in your contract interface.
4.	Observation: Look at the console (bottom of the screen). You will see a green checkmark indicating the transaction was mined into a block.
•	To Retrieve (Get Balance):
1.	Click the blue getBalance button.
2.	Observation: You will see a number appear (e.g., 1000000000000000000). This is 1 Ether in Wei (the smallest unit of Ether).
